The paper deals with interference modeling in cellular networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of MIMO beamforming also suggests a possible connection to signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the analysis of network capacity and the use of stochastic geometry suggest a possible connection to game theory (cs.GT).
